description.narrative: According to administrative data from the EPI Directorate, national DPT3 coverage is 95% with 6 districts who have less than 80% coverage. Despite the challenges of the response to measles and polio, it's an improvement compared to 2018 with 91% coverage and 17 districts reporting less than 80% DPT3 coverage. In UNICEF's six focus regions, all 40 districts reported a DPT3 coverage above 80% while in 2018, 5 districts didn't meet the target. Progress has been made in these districts in 2019 particularly in Antananarivo city. However, MICS data shows us that administrative data should be interpreted with precaution. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
